data.title: @iannagoski.bsky.social on Bluesky
data.meta_description:
Just added this late 40s Lebanese patriotic song made in Brooklyn immediately after the withdrawal of the French from the country.

The singer Nahim Simon (aka Nahum, Naaim, etc. b. 1890) was the most prolific Arabic singer of the 1910s in the U.S.

https://canary-records.bandcamp.com/track/erzeth-lebnaney
